The paper deals with lower bounds for matrix multiplication, which is a fundamental problem in computer science and has applications in many areas such as scientific computing, machine learning, and computer graphics. The paper uses techniques from computational complexity theory and numerical analysis to establish a lower bound for the required I/O when computing matrix multiplication on a processor with two layers of memory. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), cs.SC (Symbolic Computation and Formal Verification), and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
